name: FATHER BLOOPY Ginger, Baby
description:
“Houdaille's mix of swoon and croon finds him approximating an unlikely collision between Ray Davies and Devendra Banhart, a quirky combination that finds a surprisingly good fit with the densely textured mélange.” -Miami New Times

“Brightly catchy songs loaded with hooks, and pleasant surprises. A dozen tracks overflowing with dynamic pop power and good vibes.” -Dream Magazine

“One minute Roger Houdaille is Jonathan Richman jamming with Brian Eno on the title track, with similar Lou Reed talk-singing, the next he's Ray Davies doing wistful poptunes like "Pepper Tan" or "Miss Morality.” -The Big Takeover

Tracks:
1. Ginger, Baby
2. Pepper Tan
3. Baby Your Lame
4. Florida No Fault
5. Aventura
6. And I, Lover
7. Two Tays Too Today
8. What's Kamila Doing?
9. Miss Morality
10. Hot Down
11. Ginger
12. Who Pulled The Child Support?

name: MONARCS I Love You: Early Recordings
description:
Straight from the Miami rock rock rock scene came the Monarcs, a blend of musicians from other groups (Capsule, Tyranny of Shaw) who opted for a different kind of sound. However, before the tours and EPs and even their name came along, it was a secret project between the two founders Eric & Manny. With much anticipation, Dippy released two records of the old and "new" recordings under the banner I Love You. Both now out-of-print, we are happy to make them available again on this stunning collection under their new name!

TRACKLISTING:
1 For The Good Of Her
2 Courtney's Friend
3 Kellen James Has A Sick Chest Piece
4 Pave The Rainforest
5 Helen Doesn't Cry
6 Mary Disguised as Death
7 Ayami's Lost Herself
8 Suicide Love Letter Baby
9 Hold Me I'm Dead
10 Miko Amura Loves Me
BONUS
11 Beating Betty
